{
  "local_port": 35744,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "Linking your Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account can be done in several ways for convenience. Here's a step-by-step guide for each method:\n\n### 1. **Online Method (Internet Banking):**\n1. **Log in** to your SBI online banking account using your credentials.\n2. Go to the 'My Accounts' or 'Profile' section.\n3. Click on 'Link your Aadhaar number' or 'Aadhaar Registration' option.\n4. Select the relevant **account number** for which you want to link your Aadhaar.\n5. Enter your **Aadhaar number** carefully in the required field.\n6. Submit the details. You may receive a verification message on your registered mobile number.\n\n### 2. **Through SBI ATM:**\n1. Insert your **debit card** and enter your **PIN**.\n2. Select the '**Service'** option on the screen.\n3. Click on 'Aadhaar Registration'.\n4. Choose the '**Inquiries'** option.\n5. Enter your **Aadhaar number** twice for confirmation.\n6. You will receive an update regarding the linking status on your registered mobile number.\n\n### 3. **Via SMS:**\n- If your mobile number is registered with the bank, you can link Aadhaar by sending an SMS.\n- Type \u201c**UID(space)Aadhaar number(space)Account number**\u201d and send it to **567676**.\n\n### 4. **By Visiting SBI Branch:**\n1. Visit your nearest SBI branch.\n2. **Fill out the Aadhaar linking form** available at the branch.\n3. Submit the form along with a **photocopy of your Aadhaar card**. Carry the original for verification.\n4. The bank representative will process your request, and you will receive a confirmation SMS on successful linking.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Ensure your mobile number is linked with both your bank account and Aadhaar for timely notifications and successful linking.\n- Always check your account statements or confirm with customer service if the linking is successful after a few days.\n\nChoose the method that suits you best and ensure that your Aadhaar is linked for availing various benefits and subsidies offered by government schemes.",
